=========================================
LXC (LINUX CONTAINERS)
=========================================

-------------------------------------------------
1. BASIC CONCEPTS
-------------------------------------------------

LXC         = OS-level container (system container)
LXD         = Management daemon for LXC
Container   = Lightweight isolated Linux system
Image       = Template used to create containers

Unlike Docker (application containers),
LXC containers behave like lightweight virtual machines.

-------------------------------------------------
2. CONTAINER MANAGEMENT
-------------------------------------------------

# List containers
lxc list

# Launch container
lxc launch ubuntu:22.04 mycontainer

# Start container
lxc start mycontainer

# Stop container
lxc stop mycontainer

# Restart container
lxc restart mycontainer

# Delete container
lxc delete mycontainer

# Force delete
lxc delete mycontainer --force

-------------------------------------------------
3. EXECUTE COMMANDS
-------------------------------------------------

# Open shell
lxc exec mycontainer -- bash

# Run command
lxc exec mycontainer -- ls

