=========================================
DOCKER vs LXC
=========================================

Docker
------
• Application containers
• Usually one main process per container
• Uses Docker Engine (dockerd)
• Images from Docker Hub
• Best for microservices, web apps, CI/CD

LXC
---
• System containers
• Behaves like a lightweight Linux VM
• Can run multiple services (systemd, SSH, cron, etc.)
• Uses LXD/LXC tools
• Best for full Linux environments and labs

Quick Comparison

Docker Image        ≈ LXC Image
Docker Container    ≈ LXC Container
docker exec         ≈ lxc exec
docker ps           ≈ lxc list
docker logs         ≈ journalctl/logs inside container
docker inspect      ≈ lxc info / lxc config show
